\\cal N}=2$ Chern-Simons-matter theories, such that one of the\nflows ends up in the IR at a regular boson theory while its dual partner flows\nto a critical fermion theory. This construction suggests that the duality\nbetween these theories persists at finite $N$, at least when $N$ is large.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Aug 2018 19:34:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-26"}
