ng of the overall energy absorbed from the field. The joint\nangular momentum distributions of the two electrons show a highly directed\nemission of both electrons along the polarization axis as well as clear\nimprints of electron repulsion. They strongly change with the energy sharing\nbetween the electrons. The aspect of selection rules in double ionization which\nare also visible in the presented dataset has been subject to a preceding\npublication [1].\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 10 Aug 2018 13:01:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-10"}
